  "texts": [
    "For example, it is manipulative to prompt a generative AI to guilt-trip a target into donating money to a charity because the influence targets the victim's emotions and bypasses rational deliberation.",
    "11 However, important questions about the 'bypassing rationality' conceptualisation remain.",
    "While it seems accurate enough-it accounts for many paradigmatic cases of manipulation-it has been subject to severe criticism for generating false negatives (Gorin, 2014a (Gorin,, 2014b)).",
    "Some forms of manipulation-such as peer pressure or charmdo not seem to involve bypassed rationality (Baron, 2003; Noggle, 2022).",
    "Hence, the bypassing conceptualisation of manipulation does not reliably identify all manipulation cases."
  ],
